location.name: Monte negro, Rio Grande do Sul, BR (-28,606, -49,806)
PN Lagoa do Peixe--Trilha do Talha-Mar

mediaNotes: An adult male singing while the female is perched at the nest entrance. A distant male singing in the background. The focal male makes an alarm call when an aerial predator (Caracara plancus) lands in the same tree it was singing on (the series of liquid notes in quick succession.) The female answers back to the male, making the same calls.
ML: 250Hz scientific high-pass filter applied in Adobe Audition CC 2014. Second cut referred to in voice note is ML 217743.

All vocalizations were given while perched. 
This pair was also recorded by Nacho Areta (see ML 171517), but I don't believe that we recorded it simultaneously.
